> > has had this problem and if they just replaced the wire from the
> ignition or
> > found some other ingenious solution.
>
> Ned
> I doubt you need to replace the wire,, maybe the terminal ends.. and maybe
> the ignition switch...
>
> or,, you can install a hot start relay  ,the WR-1  bosch or equivalent,,
> on
> the coil circuit.
>
> the ignition switch will turn on the low current coil of the relay,, which
> will close the circuit to the ignition coil,  if you use #10 awg wire from
> the battery thru the relay to the ignition coil,, you won't have any
> voltage
> drop in the coil circuit.
>
> It might start burning your points faster with the extra current that will
> be available.
>



